---
title: Bok Choy and Black Rice Veggie Bowl with Marinated Radishes and Mushrooms
description: Black rice, like blueberries and eggplant, gets its stunning deep color from anthocyanins,  natural pigments that are also heart-healthy antioxidants. That’s not the only reason to eat it up, however—it has a delightfully nutty, earthy flavor and sturdy al dente texture. That flavor and heft make it the perfect medium for soaking up the soy and sesame-accented sauce in this recipe’s bok choy and mushroom stir-fry.
